rComments: Nima is an excellent teacher! The content of my course was really interesting and his lectures were very easy to follow. Any assignments or quizzes we had explained in depth what to expect. He is very quick and thorough with his responses if you have any questions. I definitely would retake this class!
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Graded by few things', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Sweetest prof ever. He is clear on his expectations and if you know your stuff, don't sweat.

I'm trying to be fair: he may not be the worst prof you've ever had in terms of his teaching style but his attitude is absolutely inappropriate for an academic person. He can be easily agitated and angry if you disagree with him even over a scientific matter. Although he pretends to be nice, you will find he's actually quite arrogant and entitled.

He isn't the most organized person when it comes to structuring his lectures but if you go off of what he highlights and just read the material on your own you'll be fine. He's very clear about what he wants to see. He is also understanding that we all have different perspectives. He's willing to sit with you and hear you out. He's a caring prof

He truly does care for his students and the midterms/final were pretty easy but the TAs were completely out of line and there were a lot of marking discrepancies. Lectures can also be a bit boring but overall and ok class and an easy grade.

Nima is one of my favorite profs so far. He cares about people doing well. He gives hints throughout the semester as to what will be on the exam and is very clear on what to expect. You can get easy participation/bonus marks by just showing up to class.

He is a kind person and has good intentions. Unfortunately, his in-class debates lead to personal arguments among students. He also grades without regard to different opinions and is not clear in his grading criteria.

I do not recommend taking this class with Prof. Jangouk. He is a sweet man but unfortunately, he does not know how to teach lectures properly. Lectures are basically just students giving their opinions and he doesn't actually teach anything. His expectations for the exams are unclear and the questions don't reflect student's knowledge properly.
He's not the BEST PROF EVERRRR but he's not bad either. Plus it's only his second year of teaching so can't really complain

Nima is an amazing professor. You can tell that he really enjoys teaching and he does care about the students. He uses many interesting examples to convey the material which helps us understand the concepts. If you are a serious hardworking student, you will learn a lot from his classes. I would definitely recommend him.

Good prof, lectures are interesting since he includes the whole class. Allows people to speak their opinions. Truly hits all the factors of diversity in Canada and uses lots of examples we can relate to.

The only reason he is a "good" prof is that he's easy. He is actually a really bad prof who copies the textbook word for word, rambles on and on, and is incredibly rude! If you go to class you'll get an A+, but be warned of boring lectures. Once again, rude!!!!

This prof does not know how to properly convey the material that needs to be taught during his lectures. The lectures consist of students giving their opinions about contreverial topics. He does not actually teach us anything nor does he lecture properly like other profs do. He can be rude towards students. Overall,I would not recommend this prof.

Nima is easily one of the most wholesome profs you'll ever meet. He's super sweet and cares a lot about his students. The group projects were a little bit disorganized, but this wasn't his fault and he mentioned that he would avoid doing them in future classes. Make sure you take advantage of all the bonus marks. I'd definitely recommend his class!

I've never written a review but this professor deserves my time. He is an awesome professor and definitely knows what he is doing. He demonstrated great passion when teaching this course. I hope the university give him more classes to teach in the future. Overall I recommend taking his class and make sure you attend and participate

It is his 1st year teaching and he did an amazing job. You can tell he really loves teaching this subject. Make sure you attend every lecture as he randomly does attendance. The group project was not to difficult as some groups were big only because students started to register later during the semester. Not his fault! Great Professor!

Okay teacher, really nice but sorta unorganized when it came to a group projects (groups of 15 btw) midterms are easy but he look for specific words when grading so you need to memorize his slides, his TA grade everything and they are very rude but if you go see him after class he will bump up your grade, overall he is good for a first time teacher

I loved Janouk! This is his first year teaching and you could tell he got more comfortable as the year went by He tells you exactly what will be on the midterms so its really easy to memorize and get an A+. Big group project that was VERY easy for easy marks. The exam is a take home and is not overly challenging; he wants to see us do well!

This is the sweetest prof I've ever had. New professor and just wants his students to do well. Fair grader and tells you exactly what's on the midterms and exam. There's a group project but the groups are so big, it's minimal work for each person. I would recommend taking a class with this prof to anyone.
